1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a novel real-time hyperspectral likelihood maps-aided tracking method for moving object tracking, which is a core topic in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on tracking aerial vehicles, which is a common task in robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an online learning method for generating a target model, which involves machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an adaptive fusion method for combining likelihood maps, which involves artificial intelligence techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with hyperspectral imagery, which is a type of multimedia data.
